        "payload": [
          {
            "contentString": "{patientName} is a 2-year-old girl brought in by her parents in the Czech Republic because she has been unwell with cough and fever [SNOMED:J18.9, MEDDIALOG:J18.9:0]. She looks tired and less playful than usual, with periods of fast breathing and visible shortness of breath that worry her family [SNOMED:J18.9]. Her parents have also noticed that she seems congested and occasionally has chills with the fever [SNOMED:J18.9, MEDDIALOG:J18.9:0].\n\nAt home, {patientName} is normally active, enjoys simple toddler play like stacking blocks, looking at picture books, and following her older cousins around the living room. She lives with her parents, who report no special exposures and say she usually attends routine family activities. Over the last day or two, however, she has wanted to be held more, eaten less than usual, and rested on the sofa because of fatigue [SNOMED:J18.9].\n\nHer parents describe a rattly cough that has become more frequent, especially when she is lying down, and they became more concerned when the fever persisted and her breathing seemed quicker than normal [MEDDIALOG:J18.9:0, SNOMED:J18.9]. They brought her for evaluation because pneumonia can cause cough, fever, dyspnea, tachypnea, and low oxygen levels [SNOMED:J18.9]."
          }
        ]
      }
